'''Praha''' is a [[village]] and [[municipality]] in the [[Lučenec District]] in the [[Banská Bystrica Region]] of [[Slovakia]].
Praha was founded by the [[Hussites]] in the 15th century, the name obviously being inspired by the name of [[Prague]], the [[Czechia|Czech]] capital. The Hussite tradition is also reflected on the coat of arms, which shows the characteristic Hussite chalice.
